DURBAN A Durban man who joined the French Legion will be buried with full French military honours after he died saving eight crewmen when their raft capsized during a training exercise last week.Lorenzo Rodrigues was a part of the Class of 2011 at Durban High School (DHS) and joined the French Legion two years ago.Lorenzo Rodrigues Picture: Facebook According to the school, Rodrigues managed to save eight of his crew member s lives but drowned while going back for a ninth member.He will receive a military funeral in Marseilles this week.He leaves behind his wife, Fiona and two-month old daughter, Leia.DHS have issued a statement, sending their condolences to the Rodrigues family.Source: Daily News